condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A, 2(a) | Description :Maintain a project implementation plan, including the procurement,financial management and disbursement requirements. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.A, 2(c) | Description :Ensure Implementation Team (NPIU) is led by a central Projectadvisor and assisted by adequate and qualified professional and administrative staff and not frequently replaced during the projectperiod | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.A, 2(f) | Description :Enforce the eligibility criteria for Participating States set forthin the PIP and shall only allow to participate in the Project those States which demonstrate preparedness to carry out the project.| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.A, 2(g) | Description :Ensure that the selection of the participating States, theCentrally-Sponsored Participating Institutions and the State-Sponsored institutions is transparent and in accordance with theagreed eligibil | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.A, 3(a) | Description :Make part of the proceeds of the Financing available to each of theParticipating States and each of the Centrally-Sponsored Participating Institutions under MOU between MHRD and States and CSIs. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.A, 5(a) | Description :Each State: maintain a fully operational project facilitation unit,with functions and responsibilities agreed, including inter alia the responsibility of avoid frequent staff turnover | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section I.A., 5(c) | Description :Make part of the proceeds of the Financing available to each State-SponsoredInstitutions under MOU between States and State-Sponsored institutions. | Frequency :Yearly
